    "---\n",
    "## 3. Groq API Configuration <a id='3-groq-api'></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "MediSense uses [Groq's inference API](https://console.groq.com) to run **LLaMA 3.3 70B** — the most capable open model available, delivered at sub-second inference speeds via Groq's custom LPU hardware.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why Groq + LLaMA 3.3 70B?**\n",
    "- **Speed**: Groq delivers ~750 tokens/second — critical for real-time triage\n",
    "- **Open weights**: Aligns with the hackathon's open-model ethos\n",
    "- **Medical reasoning**: LLaMA 3.3 70B shows strong performance on medical benchmarks (MedQA, PubMedQA)\n",
    "- **Free tier**: Accessible to developers in low-income countries without upfront cost\n"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "api-config-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Groq API Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Set your key via environment variable (recommended) or paste directly below\n",
    "\n",
    "GROQ_API_KEY = os.environ.get(\"GROQ_API_KEY\", \"YOUR_GROQ_API_KEY_HERE\")\n",
    "MODEL_ID     = \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\"\n",
    "MAX_TOKENS   = 1200\n",
    "TEMPERATURE  = 0.3   # Low temperature for clinical consistency\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize client\n",
    "client = Groq(api_key=GROQ_API_KEY)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Quick connectivity test\n",
    "def test_connection():\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        resp = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "            model=MODEL_ID,\n",
    "            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Reply with just: OK\"}],\n",
    "            max_tokens=5\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        return True, resp.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        return False, str(e)\n",
    "\n",
    "ok, msg = test_connection()\n",
    "status = \"✅ Connected\" if ok else \"❌ Failed\"\n",
    "print(f\"{status} — Groq API response: {msg}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Model  : {MODEL_ID}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Temp   : {TEMPERATURE}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Tokens : {MAX_TOKENS}\")"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "engine-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 4. Core Triage Engine <a id='4-triage-engine'></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "The engine is built around three components:\n",
    "1. **`PatientCase`** — a structured dataclass capturing all intake fields\n",
    "2. **`TriageResult`** — a typed dataclass for the parsed AI response\n",
    "3. **`MediSenseEngine`** — the main class handling prompt construction, API calls, and result parsing\n"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dataclasses-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Data Models ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "TriageLevel = Literal[\"LOW\", \"MODERATE\", \"HIGH\", \"EMERGENCY\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class PatientCase:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Structured patient intake form.\"\"\"\n",
    "    symptom_description : str\n",
    "    selected_tags       : list[str]      = field(default_factory=list)\n",
    "    age                 : Optional[int]  = None\n",
    "    sex                 : Optional[str]  = None   # Male / Female / Other\n",
    "    medical_history     : Optional[str]  = None\n",
    "    duration            : Optional[str]  = None\n",
    "    severity            : Optional[int]  = None   # 1–10\n",
    "\n",
    "    def to_clinical_text(self) -> str:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Compile all fields into a structured clinical summary string.\"\"\"\n",
    "        lines = []\n",
    "        if self.age:             lines.append(f\"Age: {self.age}\")\n",
    "        if self.sex:             lines.append(f\"Sex: {self.sex}\")\n",
    "        if self.medical_history: lines.append(f\"Medical History: {self.medical_history}\")\n",
    "        if self.selected_tags:   lines.append(f\"Reported symptoms: {', '.join(self.selected_tags)}\")\n",
    "        if self.symptom_description:\n",
    "            lines.append(f\"Patient description: {self.symptom_description}\")\n",
    "        if self.duration:        lines.append(f\"Duration: {self.duration}\")\n",
    "        if self.severity:        lines.append(f\"Severity score (1–10): {self.severity}\")\n",
    "        return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class TriageResult:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Parsed AI triage output.\"\"\"\n",
    "    triage       : TriageLevel\n",
    "    triage_label : str\n",
    "    summary      : str\n",
    "    conditions   : list[str]\n",
    "    steps        : str\n",
    "    red_flags    : str\n",
    "    urgent       : str\n",
    "    latency_ms   : float = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "    @property\n",
    "    def color(self) -> str:\n",
    "        return {\"LOW\": \"#39d98a\", \"MODERATE\": \"#ffb347\",\n",
    "                \"HIGH\": \"#ff7043\", \"EMERGENCY\": \"#ff2d55\"}.get(self.triage, \"#fff\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    @property\n",
    "    def emoji(self) -> str:\n",
    "        return {\"LOW\": \"🟢\", \"MODERATE\": \"🟡\",\n",
    "                \"HIGH\": \"🟠\", \"EMERGENCY\": \"🔴\"}.get(self.triage, \"⚪\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Data models defined: PatientCase, TriageResult\")"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "engine-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── MediSense Triage Engine ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "class MediSenseEngine:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Core AI triage engine powered by Groq + LLaMA 3.3 70B.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"\\\n",
    "You are MediSense, an expert AI medical triage assistant designed to support\n",
    "community health workers and patients in underserved regions who lack access\n",
    "to trained clinicians. You are NOT a replacement for a doctor.\n",
    "\n",
    "Your role is to assess symptom descriptions and assign a triage urgency level\n",
    "with supporting clinical reasoning. Be conservative — when in doubt, escalate.\n",
    "\n",
    "Respond ONLY with a valid JSON object. No markdown, no code blocks, no preamble.\n",
    "\n",
    "Required JSON schema:\n",
    "{\n",
    "  \"triage\": \"LOW\" | \"MODERATE\" | \"HIGH\" | \"EMERGENCY\",\n",
    "  \"triageLabel\": \"Human-readable label (e.g. See a Doctor Today)\",\n",
    "  \"summary\": \"2-3 sentence clinical summary of the presentation\",\n",
    "  \"conditions\": [\"Possible condition 1\", \"Possible condition 2\", \"Possible condition 3\"],\n",
    "  \"steps\": \"• Recommended action 1\\n• Recommended action 2\\n• Recommended action 3\",\n",
    "  \"redFlags\": \"• Warning sign 1\\n• Warning sign 2\\n• Warning sign 3\",\n",
    "  \"urgent\": \"If EMERGENCY: clear short action. Otherwise: empty string\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "Triage level definitions:\n",
    "- LOW: Symptoms manageable without immediate professional care. Monitor at home.\n",
    "- MODERATE: Professional evaluation needed within 24 hours.\n",
    "- HIGH: Requires clinic or hospital visit today. Do not delay.\n",
    "- EMERGENCY: Life-threatening. Call emergency services or go to ER immediately.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __init__(self, client: Groq, model: str = MODEL_ID):\n",
    "        self.client = client\n",
    "        self.model  = model\n",
    "        self.history: list[dict] = []   # For follow-up chat\n",
    "\n",
    "    def triage(self, case: PatientCase) -> TriageResult:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Run triage on a PatientCase and return a TriageResult.\"\"\"\n",
    "        user_content = f\"Please triage this patient:\\n{case.to_clinical_text()}\"\n",
    "        messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_content}]\n",
    "\n",
    "        t0 = time.time()\n",
    "        response = self.client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "            model       = self.model,\n",
    "            temperature = TEMPERATURE,\n",
    "            max_tokens  = MAX_TOKENS,\n",
    "            messages    = [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": self.SYSTEM_PROMPT}] + messages\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        latency_ms = (time.time() - t0) * 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "        raw = response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Store for follow-up conversation\n",
    "        self.history = [\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\",      \"content\": user_content},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": raw}\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Parse JSON response\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            data = json.loads(raw.replace(\"```json\", \"\").replace(\"```\", \"\").strip())\n",
    "        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n",
    "            raise ValueError(f\"LLM returned non-JSON output: {raw[:200]}...\") from e\n",
    "\n",
    "        return TriageResult(\n",
    "            triage       = data.get(\"triage\", \"MODERATE\"),\n",
    "            triage_label = data.get(\"triageLabel\", \"\"),\n",
    "            summary      = data.get(\"summary\", \"\"),\n",
    "            conditions   = data.get(\"conditions\", []),\n",
    "            steps        = data.get(\"steps\", \"\"),\n",
    "            red_flags    = data.get(\"redFlags\", \"\"),\n",
    "            urgent       = data.get(\"urgent\", \"\"),\n",
    "            latency_ms   = latency_ms\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "    def ask_followup(self, question: str) -> str:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Send a follow-up question in the context of the last triage.\"\"\"\n",
    "        if not self.history:\n",
    "            return \"Please run a triage first before asking follow-up questions.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        followup_system = \"\"\"\\\n",
    "You are MediSense, a compassionate AI health assistant. The patient has already\n",
    "received an AI triage assessment. Answer their follow-up question clearly in\n",
    "2–4 sentences. Always recommend seeing a qualified doctor for final decisions.\n",
    "Never provide a diagnosis. Be warm, clear, and empathetic.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "        messages = self.history + [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": question}]\n",
    "        response = self.client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "            model      = self.model,\n",
    "            max_tokens = 400,\n",
    "            messages   = [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": followup_system}] + messages\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        answer = response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n",
    "        self.history += [\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\",      \"content\": question},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": answer}\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "        return answer\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Instantiate the engine\n",
    "engine = MediSenseEngine(client=client)\n",
    "print(\"✅ MediSenseEngine initialized and ready.\")"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prompt-md",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5. Prompt Engineering <a id='5-prompt-engineering'></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "Effective prompt design is the backbone of reliable clinical AI. Here are the key decisions made in MediSense's prompting strategy:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **Output format** | Strict JSON schema | Ensures parseable, typed, consistent outputs every time |\n",
    "| **Temperature** | 0.3 | Low variance for clinical consistency; avoids hallucinated urgency |\n",
    "| **Role framing** | \"Expert AI triage assistant for underserved regions\" | Anchors clinical context without overstating capability |\n",
    "| **Triage definitions** | Explicit per-level descriptions in prompt | Prevents model ambiguity between MODERATE and HIGH |\n",
    "| **Conservative bias** | \"When in doubt, escalate\" | Safety-first — false negatives (missed emergencies) are worse than false positives |\n",
    "| **Disclaimer in role** | \"NOT a replacement for a doctor\" | Reduces over-reliance on AI; reinforces human-in-the-loop |\n"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
